The cabin features seating surfaces trimmed in Cognac Brown Nappa leather that extends to the dashboard, center console, and the door panels, which are joined by burl walnut wood trim accents. Amenities include a rearview camera, a Harman Kardon LOGIC7 sound system, heated and ventilated dynamic multi-contour front seats, a power rear sunshade, Distronic adaptive cruise control, Parktronic, Night View Assist, Keyless Go, dual-zone automatic climate control, and COMAND infotainment with navigation. There are signs of wear in the driver’s seat as well as an area of leather trim lifting on the right side of the dashboard.

The heated wood- and leather-rimmed steering wheel frames a digital 160-mph speedometer, a 7k-rpm tachometer, and gauges for coolant temperature and fuel level. The digital odometer indicates 110k miles. The parking assistance light intermittently illuminates.

The twin-turbocharged 5.5-liter V12 was factory rated at 510 horsepower and 612 lb-ft of torque. Power is sent to the rear wheels through a 5G-Tronic five-speed automatic transmission. A replacement transmission was reportedly installed in July 2017.
The Carfax report shows the aforementioned damage.

This 2000 BMW 328Ci coupe was purchased new by the current owner in Connecticut and has 81k miles. The car is powered by a 2.8-liter M52 inline-six paired with a five-speed manual transmission and is finished in Steel Gray Metallic over gray leather. Equipment includes five-spoke alloy wheels, a sports suspension, a sunroof, xenon headlights, heated power-adjustable front seats, and automatic climate control. This E46 coupe is now offered on dealer consignment at no reserve with a tool kit and a clean Connecticut title.

The car is finished in Steel Gray Metallic (400) and features a sunroof, xenon headlights, fog lights, power-adjustable side mirrors, and dual exhaust outlets. The windshield was replaced in preparation of the sale.

The Style 43 wheels are mounted with Continental ExtremeContact tires. The car is equipped with Dynamic Stability Control (DSC) and All Season Traction (AST), and braking is handled by four-wheel ventilated discs. The car was factory equipped with a sport-calibrated suspension. The seller states the tires were replaced in preparation of the sale.
The cabin features heated power-adjustable front seats upholstered in gray leather. Amenities include automatic climate control, a wood shift knob, a CD stereo, and cruise control.

The multi-function leather-wrapped steering wheel frames a 155-mph speedometer, a tachometer with an inset fuel economy gauge, and gauges for coolant temperature and fuel level. The digital odometer indicates 81k miles.
The 2.8-liter M52TUB28 inline-six was factory rated at 193 horsepower and 206 lb-ft of torque.
Power is sent to the rear wheels through a five-speed manual transmission. The Carfax report notes that the clutch was replaced in 2021.
The Carfax report shows no accidents or damage.

This 1972 Chevrolet El Camino is powered by a replacement 396ci V8 linked with a four-speed manual transmission, and it is finished in black with white rally stripes and a black vinyl roof cover. Equipment includes a cowl-induction hood, 15″ five-spoke wheels, Mickey Thompson tires, front disc brakes, and power steering, while the engine is fitted with an Edelbrock intake manifold, a Holley four-barrel carburetor, aluminum cylinder heads, long-tube headers, Flowmaster mufflers, and MSD ignition components. The cabin is trimmed in black vinyl and outfitted with air conditioning, a tilt steering wheel, a cassette stereo, and power windows. Acquired by the selling dealer in 2022, this El Camino is offered with a Virginia title.

The pickup is finished in black with a matching vinyl roof cover and white rally stripes. Exterior details include a cowl-induction hood with locking hood pins as well as a drop-down tailgate, SS 396 badging, and chrome bumpers and trim.

Five-spoke 15″ wheels are mounted with Mickey Thompson tires measuring 275/60 out back. The car is equipped with power steering, and stopping is provided by power-assisted front disc and rear drum brakes.

The bucket seats are upholstered in black vinyl and joined by a color-coordinated dashboard, door panels, and carpeting. Amenities include a center console, power windows, SS badging, a Hurst shifter, a cassette radio, and air conditioning.

The SS-branded steering wheel sits on a tilting column and fronts a 120-mph speedometer, a tachometer, an analog clock, and readouts for amperage, coolant temperature, and fuel level. An aftermarket oil pressure gauge is mounted below the dashboard. The five-digit odometer shows 14k miles, and the total mileage is unknown.
The replacement 396ci V8 is equipped with an Edelbrock intake manifold, a Holley four-barrel carburetor, aluminum cylinder heads, and MSD ignition components.
Power is routed to the rear wheels through a four-speed manual transmission. Long-tube headers flow to a dual exhaust system with Flowmaster mufflers.

This 2005 Lexus GX470 is finished in Dorado Gold Pearl over Ivory leather upholstery and is powered by a 4.7-liter 2UZ-FE V8 that drives all four wheels through a five-speed automatic transmission, a dual-range transfer case, and a Torsen locking center differential. Equipment includes fog lights, a power sunroof, a roof rack, illuminated running boards, a receiver hitch, 17″ double five-spoke alloy wheels, heated power-adjustable front seats, third-row seating, dual-zone automatic climate control, a six-disc CD stereo, navigation, a Mark Levinson sound system, a rear-seat entertainment system, and cruise control. It was purchased by the seller in 2023 following registration history in Michigan and Ohio and now has 134k miles.  This J120 GX470 is offered at no reserve with a clean Carfax report and a clean Ohio title in the seller’s name.

The vehicle is finished in Dorado Gold Pearl (587) with body-color wheel arch extensions. Additional exterior details include fog lights, a power sunroof, illuminated running boards, heated power-adjustable side mirrors, a roof rack, a receiver hitch, and a rear wiper. There is a scratch around the left rear wheel arch, and close-up photographs of the exterior finish and trim are shown in the gallery below.

The 17″ double five-spoke alloy wheels are mounted with 265/65 Michelin Defender LTX tires that have 2020 date codes. The vehicle is equipped with a Kinetic Dynamic Suspension System (KDSS) with independent wheel articulation.

The heated power-adjustable front seats are upholstered in Ivory leather, and wood trim accents the cabin. Amenities include third-row seating, dual-zone automatic climate control, a six-disc CD stereo, navigation, a Mark Levinson sound system, a rear-seat entertainment system, and cruise control.

The leather- and wood-rimmed multifunction steering wheel is mounted on a power-adjustable column and fronts a 130-mph speedometer, a 7k-rpm tachometer, and supplementary gauges. The digital odometer indicates 134k miles, approximately 4,500 of which were added under current ownership.

The 4.7-liter 2UZ-FE V8 features VVT-i variable valve timing and was rated at 270 horsepower and 330 lb-ft of torque when new. The timing belt, drive belts, and water pump were replaced in March 2023.

Power is routed to all four wheels through a five-speed automatic transmission, a dual-range transfer case, and a Torsen locking center differential. The seller states that the rear cross-member and trailer hitch were replaced due to corrosion in 2023, and an undercoating has been applied to the frame.
The Carfax report is free of accidents or other reported damage.

This 1970 Saab 96 V4 was acquired in 2016 by the current owner, a Saab collector in the Chicago area, and it is finished in beige over tan vinyl upholstery. Powered by a 1.5-liter V4 mated to a column-shifted four-speed manual transaxle, the car is equipped with 15″ steel wheels, front disc brakes, chrome-plated bumpers and trim, front bucket seats, pop-out rear windows, and a heater. This 96 is now offered at no reserve by the seller on behalf of the owner with an owner’s manual, a tool roll, service records, a calendar featuring the car, and a clean Illinois title in the owner’s name.

The seller states that the car was finished in the factory shade of Savannah Beige (Y6) under previous ownership. Exterior details include Saab C-pillar badges, rear mud flaps, and chrome-plated bumpers with overriders. Rust bubbles are noted on the left side of the rear valance, an area of rust is present on the inner bottom corner of the left door, and exterior blemishes are documented in the walk-around video below.
Silver-painted 15″ steel wheels wear polished hubcaps and are mounted with older 165-series Dunlop SP 20 A/S tires. Stopping power is provided by front disc and rear drum brakes.

The cabin houses front bucket seats and a rear bench trimmed in tan vinyl upholstery as well as color-coordinated door panels and carpets. A carpeted dashboard pad has been installed, and additional appointments include black floor mats, a heater, three-point front seat belts, and rear lap belts. The rubber liner on the inner left-front wheel well is discolored and cracking, and there is a crack in the top of the dashboard pad.

A two-spoke steering wheel is wrapped in an aftermarket vinyl cover, and it fronts a 100-mph VDO speedometer, a clock, and gauges for fuel level and engine temperature. The five-digit odometer has rolled over and now shows 3k miles.
The 1.5-liter Ford V4 features a Weber single-barrel carburetor.
Power is sent to the front wheels via a column-shifted four-speed manual transaxle. Rust on the edges of the floor pans is visible in the gallery below.
Service records, an owner’s manual, a tool roll, and a calendar featuring the car are included in the sale.

This 2002 Mercedes-Benz ML500 is powered by a 5.0-liter V8 linked to a five-speed automatic transmission and a dual-range transfer case, and it is finished in Brilliant Silver Metallic over Ash leather. Features include a glass sunroof, power rear-quarter windows, xenon headlights, 17″ six-spoke alloy wheels, heated power-adjustable front seats, front-seat position memory, folding second-row seats, navigation, a Bose sound system, tinted windows, cruise control, and automatic climate control. This W163 has 53k miles and is now offered by the selling dealer at no reserve with the owner’s manual, a stamped maintenance log, a clean Carfax report, and a clean New Jersey title.

The exterior is finished in Brilliant Silver Metallic (744) with matching bumpers and side moldings as well as heated power-folding side mirrors with integrated turn signals. Additional details include xenon headlights, a glass sunroof, fog lights, tinted windows, roof rails, a rear wiper with a washer, and a single exhaust outlet.

The 17″ six-spoke alloy wheels are mounted with Kumho tires. The truck is equipped with an independent double-wishbone suspension, and stopping power is provided by disc brakes at all four corners. The anti-lock brake pump was replaced in preparation for the sale along with the brake fluid and the rear brake calipers, rotors, and hoses.

The cabin features heated power-adjustable front seats with position memory trimmed in Ash leather, and burl wood trim accents the dash and doors. Interior amenities include folding second-row seats, power rear-quarter windows, a lockable safe, a fold-down infotainment screen, navigation, a Bose sound system, cruise control, and automatic climate control. The cabin air filter was replaced in preparation for the sale.
The steering wheel frames a 150-mph speedometer, a 7k-rpm tachometer, and gauges for coolant temperature and fuel level. The digital odometer indicates 53k miles.
The 5.0-liter M113 V8 was factory rated at 288 horsepower and 325 lb-ft of torque. Work in preparation for the sale has included fluids services and replacing the fuel filter.
Power is routed to all four wheels via a five-speed automatic transmission and a dual-range transfer case. The transmission conductor plate and pilot bushing
The Carfax report shows no accidents or damage.

This 1970 Volkswagen Karmann Ghia coupe is powered by an air-cooled 1,776cc flat-four and was acquired by the seller in April 2022. Subsequent work included converting the car from a semi-automatic transaxle to a four-speed manual, refreshing the upholstery, repainting the body in Pampas Yellow, and fitting 15″ Fuchs-style wheels, dropped spindles, and an adjustable axle beam. Additional details include front disc brakes, a CB Performance Maganspark ignition system, a BMD serpentine belt kit, a full-flow oiling system, a Monza-style exhaust system, front lap belts, faux woodgrain dashboard trim, and a wire basket with integrated cupholders. This Karmann Ghia coupe is now offered with refurbishment records and a clean California title in the seller’s name.

The car left the factory finished in Pampas Yellow (L10E) and received a repaint and replacement seals under current ownership. Exterior details include a left side-view mirror, tinted windows, polished trim, pop-out rear quarter windows, a Karmann badge on the right front fender, and chrome bumpers with overriders. The latch on the fuel filler door is broken.

Fuchs-style 15″ alloy wheels are mounted with 155/60 Kumho tires up front and 165/65 Continental rubber out back. The car has been lowered by reindexing the rear torsion arms and installing an adjustable front axle beam and replacement spindles. Stopping power is provided by front discs and rear drums.

The low-back front bucket seats and folding rear bench are trimmed in tan vinyl and beige cloth upholstery. Interior elements include black door panels and carpeting, front lap belts, faux woodgrain dashboard trim, and a wire basket with integrated cupholders. The horn, cassette stereo, dome light, and rear window defroster are inoperative.

The two-spoke steering wheel wears an aftermarket wrap and frames a 90-mph speedometer and a fuel-level gauge. The five-digit mechanical odometer shows 65k miles, and true mileage is unknown. The analog clock does not work.

The replacement air-cooled 1,776cc flat-four is fed by a single downdraft carburetor topped with an oil bath air cleaner and is equipped with a CB Performance Maganspark ignition system, a BMD serpentine belt kit, a full-flow oiling system, and a Monza-style exhaust system with heater boxes. The engine leaks oil.
Initially outfitted with an Automatic Stickshift semi-automatic transaxle, the car now delivers power to the rear wheels through a four-speed manual transaxle.

This 2012 Lexus GX460 is a Canadian-market example that was recently acquired by the selling dealer and now has 73k kilometers (~45k miles). The truck is finished in black over black leather upholstery and is powered by a 4.6-liter V8 linked with a six-speed automatic transmission, a dual-range transfer case, and a locking center differential. Equipment includes 18″ six-spoke alloy wheels, running boards, heated and ventilated front seats, a sunroof, a Mark Levinson sound system, and navigation. This J150 GX460 is offered by the selling dealer in Canada with the owner’s manual, a clean Carfax report, and British Columbia registration.
The truck is finished in black, and exterior equipment includes a sunroof, heated power-adjustable side mirrors, running boards, roof rails, and a flip-up rear window.

The 18″ six-spoke alloy wheels are mounted with Michelin Premier LTX tires. The truck is equipped with an Adaptive Variable Suspension (AVS) and adaptive rear air suspension with automatic load leveling. Stopping power is provided by four-wheel disc brakes.

The cabin houses heated and ventilated power-adjustable front seats and a heated second-row bench upholstered in black leather that extends to the center armrest and door panels. Other interior details include third-row seats, a 10.3″ touchscreen multimedia system, navigation, a Mark Levinson sound system, and three-zone automatic climate control.

The leather- and wood-trimmed steering wheel fronts a 200-km/h speedometer, a tachometer with a 5,900-rpm redline, and gauges for coolant temperature and fuel level. The digital odometer indicates 73k kilometers (~45k miles).
The 4.6-liter 1UR-FE DOHC V8 features VVT-i variable valve timing and was factory rated at 301 horsepower and 329 lb-ft of torque. An oil change was performed in preparation for the sale.
Power is routed to all four wheels through a six-speed automatic transmission, a dual-range transfer case, and a Torsen limited-slip center differential with an electronic differential lock.
The Carfax report is free of accidents or other reported damage.
The vehicle does not have a title and is being sold on its British Columbia registration, which serves as the ownership document in British Columbia, Canada.

This 2023 Porsche 911 GT3 RS is finished in GT Silver Metallic over black leather and Race-Tex and is powered by a 4.0-liter flat-six that drives the rear wheels through a seven-speed PDK dual-clutch transaxle and an electronically locking differential. A front-axle lift system was specified, and features also include rear-axle steering, LED headlights, carbon-fiber full bucket seats, a rear swan-neck-hinged wing with DRS, and center-locking satin black 20″ and 21″ forged aluminum wheels. The current owner acquired the car in May 2024 and it now has 850 miles. This 992 GT3 RS is now offered in California on dealer consignment with a window sticker, service records, an accident-free Carfax report, and a clean Nevada title.

The car is finished in GT Silver Metallic (M7Z) and features a rear swan-neck-hinged wing with drag-reduction (DRS) functionality as well as LED headlights, a rear fog light, dual center-exit exhaust outlets, and Exclusive Design taillights. The windshield was replaced in December 2023 and the dealer states that 3M paint protection film has been applied to the full exterior at a cost of approximately $8k.

Satin black-finished 20” front and 21” rear GT3 RS forged lightweight aluminum wheels are mounted with Pirelli P Zero Corsa tires measuring 275/35 and 335/30, respectively. The car is equipped with rear-axle steering and a front-axle lift system. Stopping power is provided by dimpled and ventilated discs at each corner.

The cabin features carbon-fiber full bucket seats trimmed in black leather with matching Race-Tex inserts as well as GT Silver stitching and GT3 RS headrest embroidery. Interior appointments include Porsche Communication Management (PCM) infotainment, Silver Grey seatbelts, and GT3 RS-branded illuminated carbon-fiber door sill guards. A fire extinguisher is mounted in the passenger footwell.

The GT3 sports steering wheel features a yellow centering stripe, paddle shifters, and a vehicle configuration dial, and it frames a Racing Yellow-ringed central tachometer with a 9k-rpm redline as well as a digital speed readout and dual adjustable TFT screens. This example was ordered with a white Sport Chrono dial. The digital odometer indicates 850 miles.

The 4.0-liter flat-six features direct fuel injection, VarioCam variable valve timing, dry-sump lubrication, and individual throttle bodies. It was rated at 518 horsepower and 342 lb-ft of torque. The oil was most recently changed in December 2023.
Power is sent to the rear wheels through a seven-speed PDK dual-clutch transaxle and an electronically locking differential. The car was ordered with a 23.7-gallon fuel tank.

The window sticker notes initial delivery to Porsche Minneapolis in Minnesota and lists factory equipment, colors, options, and a total price of $242,980. Manufacturer’s literature and service records are also included in the sale.
The Carfax report notes at least one recall and voluntary service action.

This 2013 Porsche Cayenne Diesel is finished in Umber Metallic over Light Tartufo and Umber leather and is powered by a 3.0-liter turbodiesel V6 linked with an eight-speed Tiptronic S automatic transmission and a locking center differential. Equipment includes the Premium Plus, Bose Audio, and Walnut Interior packages as well as 19″ Cayenne Design II wheels, heated and ventilated power-adjustable front seats, heated rear seats, and dual-zone automatic climate control. The SUV has remained registered in California since new, and it now has 88k miles. Recently acquired by the selling dealer, this Cayenne Diesel is now offered in Nevada at no reserve with a Porsche Production Specifications document, the owner’s manual, and a clean California title.

The vehicle is finished in Umber Metallic with black trim and features a receiver hitch, a power sunroof, fog lights, dual exhaust outlets, LED taillights, and front and rear ParkAssist sensors. The Carfax report notes that the right side and right front of the vehicle sustained “minor damage” in September 2021 with no additional information provided.

The 19″ Cayenne Design II alloy wheels are mounted with 265/50 Michelin Latitude Tour HP tires. Stopping power is provided by six-piston front and four-piston rear brake calipers over ventilated rotors at each corner.

The cabin features heated and ventilated power-adjustable front seats and a rear bench upholstered in Light Tartufo leather joined by a two-tone Umber and Light Tartufo dashboard, center console, and door panels. Wood trim adorns the interior, and other appointments include a Bose sound system, a touchscreen CD stereo, dual-zone automatic climate control, and powered rear sunshades. The driver’s seat bottom is worn.

The heated leather-wrapped steering wheel features shifter switches and frames a central tachometer, a 175-mph speedometer, a configurable digital display, and gauges for oil temperature, oil pressure, coolant temperature, and fuel level. The digital odometer indicates 88k miles.

The 3.0-liter turbodiesel V6 was factory rated at 240 horsepower and 406 lb-ft of torque. Power is sent to all four wheels through an eight-speed Tiptronic S automatic transmission and a locking center differential.
The Porsche Production Specifications document notes a production completion date of February 14, 2013, and lists factory colors and options.
The Carfax report notes the aforementioned damage entry and at least one recall.

This 1978 Ford Pinto Wagon is finished in green with woodgrain appliques over green vinyl upholstery and is powered by a 2.3-liter OHC inline-four paired with a three-speed automatic transmission. Equipment includes a bright grille, rear hatch spoiler, chrome bumpers, power-assisted rack-and-pinion steering, front disc brakes, body-color wheel covers, and a multi-plex AM/FM stereo. The car was acquired by the seller in 2022. This Pinto Wagon is now offered at no reserve in Virginia with a Montana title in the name of the seller’s LLC.

The body is finished in green with woodgrain appliques along the bodyside and liftgate. Details include a bright grille, a fender-mounted antenna, a rear hatch spoiler, and chrome bumpers. Paint and vinyl applique blemishes are displayed in the gallery. The left mirror glass is broken and portions are missing.

The 13” wheels wear body-colored hubcaps and are wrapped in 175/70 Barum Brillantis 2 tires. The car is equipped with power-assisted rack-and-pinion steering as well as power-assisted front disc brakes and rear drums.

The front bucket seats and folding rear seats are upholstered in green vinyl. Woodgrain trim lines the dashboard and surrounds the floor-mounted shifter, and equipment includes a cabin heater, a multiplex AM/FM stereo, and rubber floor mats.

The two-spoke steering wheel frames an 85mph speedometer, a fuel level gauge, and an array of warning lights. The mechanical odometer shows 64k miles, approximately 500 of which were added under current ownership.
The 2.3-liter inline-four OHC was factory rated at 88 horsepower and 118 lb-ft of torque.
Power is sent to the rear wheels through a three-speed automatic transmission. Corrosion is visible on underbody components.

This 1985 Honda ATC 70 was first sold by Honda-Kawasaki of Lemon Grove, California, and remained in the state with the family of its original owner until the seller acquired it in 2023. Subsequent work included refinishing the 7″ steel wheels and exhaust and replacing the blue vinyl solo seat, steering stem bearings, tires, fuel lines, and more as detailed below. Power comes from a 72cc OHC four-stroke single mated to a four-speed transmission with an automatic clutch, and the three-wheeler is equipped with an enclosed drive chain, a recoil starter, a rear drum brake, a thumb throttle, and a 1.1-gallon fuel tank finished in red. This ATC 70 is now offered at no reserve with initial purchase documents and a clean Arizona title in the seller’s name.

The three-wheeler is finished in red with two-tone blue Honda decals and features a 1.1-gallon fuel tank, a chrome rear grab bar, plastic fenders, and rubber-covered foot pegs. A blue vinyl solo seat was installed and the rear decal and fuel filler cap gasket were replaced following the seller’s acquisition. A blemish on the lower-left area of the fuel tank is noted by the seller.

The 7″ steel wheels were refinished in silver and mounted with replacement knobby tires in 2023, and the steering stem bearings were also replaced at that time. Stopping power is provided by a drum brake mounted to the rear axle. The three-wheeler is not equipped with suspension.

The chrome-finished handlebar was fitted with replacement grips under current ownership, and it is equipped with a thumb-actuated throttle, an ignition cutoff switch, and a front brake lever. The ATC is not equipped with an odometer or other instrumentation, therefore total mileage is unknown.

The air-cooled 72cc OHC four-stroke single is equipped with a recoil starter, a 13mm piston-valve carburetor, magneto ignition, and an exhaust system with a perforated heat shield that exits below the rear fenders. Power is delivered to the rear wheels through a four-speed transmission with an automatic clutch as well as an enclosed drive chain. Work following the seller’s acquisition included flushing the fuel system, replacing the spark plug and fuel lines, and refinishing the exhaust system.

The car left the factory finished in Bermuda Blue and was refinished under prior ownership. Exterior equipment includes a power-operated white convertible soft top, a color-keyed Endura front bumper, quad headlights, a scooped hood, a hood-mounted tachometer, a rear wing, and quad exhaust outlets.

The 15″ Rally II wheels are mounted with 245/60 BFGoodrich Radial T/A white-letter tires. A full-size spare is located in the trunk. The car is equipped with power steering, and braking is handled by power-assisted front discs and rear drums.

Originally trimmed in blue vinyl, the cabin now houses bucket seats and a rear bench upholstered in white with blue accents on the dash and center console. Amenities include a padded dashboard, an AM/FM stereo, and faux woodgrain trim on the instrument panel and center console. The belt for the air conditioning compressor is removed, and the air conditioning does not work.

The three-spoke steering wheel frames a 140-mph speedometer flanked by an analog clock and a combination gauge indicating engine temperature, oil pressure, and fuel level. The five-digit odometer shows 29k miles, approximately 10 of which were added under current ownership.
The 400ci V8 is equipped with a single four-barrel carburetor and was factory rated at 350 horsepower.
Power is routed to the rear wheels through a three-speed automatic transmission. A replacement dual exhaust system is installed.
Decoding the trim tag reveals the following information:
The Pontiac Historic Services documentation, including a copy of the build sheet, will accompany the car.

This 1995 Mercedes-Benz E320 coupe remained registered in Quebec through a previous listing on BaT in August 2023 and it now shows 165k kilometers (~103k miles). It is finished in Spruce Green Metallic over Saffron leather upholstery and is powered by a 3.2-liter M104 inline-six paired with a four-speed automatic transmission. Equipment includes a power-operated sunroof, eight-hole 15″ wheels, heated power-adjustable front seats, driver’s seat position memory, central locking, and power windows and side mirrors. Acquired by the selling dealer in 2024, this C124 E320 coupe is offered in Canada at no reserve with service records, a clean Carfax report, and Ontario registration.

The car is finished in Spruce Green Metallic (249) with color-matched lower cladding. Features include a power-operated sunroof, a mono-blade windshield wiper, and a power antenna and side mirrors. The antenna was repaired in July 2024. A blemish is noted on the bottom right rear window, and close-up photos of the paintwork and trim are presented in the gallery.

The 15″ wheels are mounted with 195/65 older Michelin Pilot Exalto A/S tires that the selling dealer states are in fair condition. Braking is handled by ventilated front and solid rear disc brakes with ABS.

The heated power-adjustable front seats are upholstered in Saffron leather (264) and are accompanied by a color-coordinated lower dashboard, center console, door panels, and carpets. Interior appointments include driver’s seat position memory, central locking, rubber floor mats, a passenger airbag, and power windows. A factory CD changer is located in the trunk. The air conditioning was recharged in preparation for the sale. The cruise control system is inoperative and the selling dealer notes cracks in the wood console trim.

The leather-wrapped airbag steering wheel frames VDO instrumentation consisting of a 260-km/h speedometer and a tachometer as well as an analog clock and gauges for coolant temperature, oil pressure, and fuel level. The six-digit odometer shows 165k kilometers (~103k miles), approximately 300 of which were added under current ownership.
The 3.2-liter M104 inline-six was factory rated at 217 horsepower and 229 lb-ft of torque. The spark plugs were changed in July 2024.
Power is sent to the rear wheels through a four-speed automatic transmission.
The Carfax report shows no accidents or other damage.
The vehicle does not have a title and is being sold on its registration, which serves as the ownership document in Ontario, Canada.

This 1998 Honda Acty SDX is a right-hand-drive pickup that is said to have been used by a fire department near Kobe, Japan, before being imported to the US in 2024. It is finished in red over gray cloth and powered by an E07A 656cc inline-three paired with a five-speed manual transaxle. It features four-wheel drive, 13″ powder-coated wheels, Honda vinyl graphics, an emergency beacon, front disc brakes, a work light, drop sides, mud flaps, a radio, and a cabin heater. Accompanying the truck is a 1981 Honda CT70 that is powered by a replacement 125cc four-stroke single paired with a four-speed manual transmission. This Acty SDX is now offered at no reserve by the selling dealer with an owner’s manual, service records, and a clean Washington title for the Acty.

The truck is said to have been refinished in red in Japan and features a work light, a tailgate and drop sides, front window visors, and mud flaps. Additional equipment includes white Honda vinyl graphics, yellow fog lights, a roof-mounted emergency beacon, and a rack-mounted spare fuel can. A wheel chock, tie-down straps, and a folding aluminum ramp accompany the truck. There are scratches on the truck bed and the left-side tailgate rubber bump stop is missing.
The Honda VX 13″ wheels were powder-coated white and mounted with 165/80 Forceum tires. Braking is provided by front discs and rear drums.

The seating surfaces are upholstered in gray cloth, and interior equipment includes a radio and a cabin heater. There are oil stains on the passenger seat and the siren for the CB radio was removed before the truck was imported.

The two-spoke steering wheel is situated at the right side of the cabin and frames a 130-km/h speedometer, which displays recommended shift points and is flanked gauges for coolant temperature and fuel level. The six-digit odometer shows 5k kilometers (~3,700 miles), fewer than 30 of which were added under current ownership.
The E07A 656cc inline-three was factory rated at 38 horsepower and 40 lb-ft of torque. The fluids were changed and the battery replaced in June 2024.
Power is sent to the rear or all four wheels through a five-speed manual transaxle.

The CT70 features a hollow T-bone frame, and this example is finished in white with black, red, and white graphics along with white fenders. Equipment includes a solo seat, a headlight, 10″ wheels, a conventional fork, drum brakes, and a side stand.
Twist-locking folding handlebars frame a replacement Nippon Seiki 50-mph speedometer that displays recommended shift points. The five-digit odometer shows 5k miles, and the total mileage is unknown.

The replacement 125cc four-stroke single features a kick starter, electronic ignition, a sidedraft carburetor, and an upswept exhaust system with a chrome-finished heat shield. Power is sent to the rear wheel through a four-speed manual transmission as well as a drive chain protected by a black-finished guard.
The CT70 does not have a title or registration and is being sold on a bill of sale only.
The Acty’s Washington title is noted as a duplicate.

description: This 1974 Honda CL360 Scrambler is finished in Muscat Green Metallic and is powered by a 356cc parallel twin paired with a six-speed transmission. Features include dual Keihin carburetors, both kick and electric starters, a chrome high-mount dual exhaust system, drum brakes, 18″ wire-spoke wheels, street lighting, chrome fenders, a cross-braced handlebar, and a two-up seat. The current owner purchased the bike in 2022, and service in preparation for the sale consisted of changing the oil, cleaning the carburetors, adjusting the valves, setting the ignition timing, and replacing the battery. This CL360 Scrambler is offered at no reserve by the seller on behalf of the current owner with a clean Minnesota title in the owner’s name.

The 2.9-gallon fuel tank and side covers are finished in Muscat Green Metallic with black graphics. Equipment includes chrome fenders, street lighting, a black vinyl two-up seat, and both center and side stands.

Chrome-finished 18″ rims are laced to drum-brake hubs and are mounted with older Bridgestone tires that have cracks in the sidewalls. Suspension consists of a telescopic fork as well as dual shocks mounted to the tubular swingarm.

The chrome cross-braced handlebar carries dual mirrors and is mounted aft of a Nippon Seiki 110-mph speedometer and a matching tachometer with a 9,200-rpm redline. The five-digit odometer shows 3,800 miles, less than 100 of which were ridden under current ownership.

The 356cc parallel twin was factory rated at 34 horsepower and features dual Keihin carburetors, both kick and electric starters, and a high-mounted dual exhaust system with slotted and perforated chrome heat shields. Work in 2024 included changing the oil, cleaning the carburetors, adjusting the valves, setting the ignition timing, and replacing the battery.
Power is sent to the rear wheel through a multi-plate wet clutch, a six-speed transmission, and a drive chain with a black upper guard.

This 2012 Mercedes-Benz E63 AMG wagon is finished in Designo Alanite Gray Magno over black leather and is powered by a twin-turbocharged 5.5-liter M157 V8 linked to a seven-speed MCT automatic transmission. Equipment includes a panoramic sunroof, black 19″ AMG wheels, a back-up camera, heated and ventilated power front seats, dual-zone automatic climate control, and COMAND with navigation. The car has spent time in Texas and Ohio and now has under 80k miles. Recently acquired by the selling dealer, this S212 AMG wagon is now offered in Virginia at no reserve with a clean Carfax report and a clean Ohio title.

The car is finished in Designo Alanite Gray Magno (044) and features AMG-specific bodywork. Exterior details include a panoramic sunroof, roof rails, a rear window wiper, a rear diffuser, quad exhaust outlets, and bi-xenon headlights with Active Curve Illumination. Black vinyl wrap has been added to the roof panel, and the selling dealer notes evidence of paintwork on the hood.

Black powder-coated 19″ AMG double-spoke alloy wheels are mounted with Kumho Ecsta PS91 tires measuring 255/35 up front and 285/30 out back. Stopping power is provided by AMG-branded calipers fitted over cross-drilled and slotted rotors at each corner. The car is equipped with an adjustable air suspension system. The Carfax report notes air suspension compressor repairs in May 2016.

The cabin features heated and ventilated power-adjustable front seats that are trimmed in black leather complemented by carbon-fiber trim. Amenities include a back-up camera, Keyless Go, a Harman Kardon sound system, dual-zone automatic climate control, powered rear sunshades, and COMAND infotainment with navigation. The driver’s seat active multi-contour operations do not work.

The AMG sport steering wheel features paddle shifters and frames a 200-mph speedometer and a tachometer with a 6,400-rpm redline as well as gauges for coolant temperature and fuel level. The digital odometer indicates under 80k miles.

The twin-turbocharged 5.5-liter M157 V8 features direct injection as well as variable valve timing and was factory rated at 518 horsepower and 516 lb-ft of torque. The selling dealer states that the catalytic converters have been replaced.
Power is sent to the rear wheels through a seven-speed MCT automatic transmission.
The Carfax report is free of accidents or other reported damage.

This 2000 BMW 740i is an Orient Blue Metallic example that remained with its first owner until 2019 and was acquired by the current owner on BaT in 2021. Power comes from a 4.4-liter V8 mated to a five-speed automatic transmission, and equipment includes a glass sunroof, 18″ M-Parallel wheels, xenon headlights, clear corner lenses, Sand Beige Montana leather upholstery, heated front and rear seats, a heated and power-adjustable steering wheel, and a Sony touchscreen stereo with Apple CarPlay connectivity and a rear-view camera. This E38 has 107k miles and is now offered at no reserve on dealer consignment with manufacturer’s literature and a Texas title.

The car is finished in Orientblau Metallic (317) with matching body moldings and black window trim as well as a glass sunroof, xenon headlights with washers, fog lights, and aftermarket front corner lenses. There is evidence of paintwork on the fenders, hood, bumpers, and rocker panels, and the Carfax report notes damage occurring in December 2023. The sunroof drains were cleared in 2023 at which time the seal was replaced.

Five-spoke 18″ M-Parallel wheels are mounted with Continental ExtremeContact Sport Plus tires displaying 2017 date codes. Standard features included Dynamic Brake Control and Dynamic Stability Control, and cross-drilled and slotted rotors are fitted at each corner. The power steering lines were replaced under current ownership along with the upper rear control arms and the front thrust rod bushings.

The power-adjustable and heated front seats are upholstered in Sand Beige Montana leather and equipped with adjustable lumbar support and memory settings for the driver. Additional amenities include cruise control, automatic climate control, heated rear seats, black M-branded floor mats, a CD changer, and a Sony touchscreen stereo with Apple CarPlay connectivity and a rear-view camera mounted on the trunk lid. A cupholder was replaced under current ownership along with the driver window regulator.

The heated and power-adjustable steering wheel frames a 155-mph speedometer, a tachometer with an inset fuel economy indicator, and additional gauges displaying fuel level and coolant temperature. The digital odometer indicates 107k miles, approximately 7k of which were added under current ownership.

The 4.4-liter M62TUB44 V8 was factory rated at 282 horsepower and 324 lb-ft of torque. The oil was most recently changed in November 2022, at which time the coolant was flushed. The rear main seal, alternator, and coolant pump were replaced in 2023.
Power is sent to the rear wheels through a ZF five-speed automatic transmission. The transmission output shaft seal was replaced in November 2022.
The Carfax report shows the aforementioned damage entry.
The Texas title is noted as a Certified Copy.

This 2017 Aston Martin V12 Vantage S is a Canadian-market example that has 12k kilometers (~7k miles) and was ordered through the Q by Aston Martin program. Finished in Spectre Silver over Maltese Blue and Spicy Red upholstery, it is powered by a 5.9-liter V12 paired with a seven-speed manual transaxle. The car has carbon-fiber exterior and interior accents, a limited-slip differential, xenon headlights, carbon-ceramic disc brakes, Graphite Diamond Turned 19″ multi-spoke alloy wheels, parking sensors, a One-77 steering wheel, a backup camera, heated power-adjustable seats with position memory settings, a Bang & Olufsen sound system, and navigation. Acquired by the selling dealer in 2024, this V12 Vantage S is now offered with the owner’s manual, a car cover, clean US and Canadian Carfax reports, and Manitoba registration.

The car is finished in Q Exclusive Spectre Silver and has xenon headlights with washers, a vented hood, swan-hinged doors, flush-mount door handles, an aluminum fuel filler cap, power-folding side mirrors, front and rear parking sensors, integrated dual exhaust outlets, Q badging, and a red satin carbon-fiber front splitter, grille, diffuser, mirror caps, taillight infills, side strakes, and hood vents. The front splitter is damaged.

Graphite Diamond Turned 19″ multi-spoke alloy wheels are mounted with 255/35 front and 295/30 rear Pirelli P Zero tires. The car is equipped with an Adaptive Damping System (ADS), Emergency Brake Assist (EBA), and Dynamic Stability Control (DSC). Braking is provided by red Aston-Martin-branded calipers over carbon-ceramic two-piece rotors at all four corners.

The heated power-adjustable seats are upholstered in Maltese Blue leather with Aston Martin logos embroidered on the headrests, Spicy Red stripes, and color-contrasting stitching that extends to the dashboard, center console, and door panels. Carbon-fiber trim accents the cabin, and additional appointments include carpeted floor mats, glass switches, an Arctic Blue Alcantara headliner, navigation, a backup camera, a Bang & Olufsen sound system, a CD stereo, cruise control, carbon-fiber door sill plates, seat position memory settings, carbon-fiber grab handles, and automatic climate control.

The One-77 steering wheel frames a 330-km/h speedometer and a reverse-sweep 8k-rpm tachometer as well as gauges for coolant temperature and fuel level. The digital odometer indicates 12k kilometers (~7k miles).
The 5.9-liter DOHC V12 was factory rated at 565 horsepower and 457 lb-ft of torque.
Power is routed to the rear wheels via a seven-speed manual transaxle with a dogleg first-gear pattern and a limited-slip differential. Additional photos of the underside are provided in the gallery.
The US and Canadian Carfax reports are free of accidents or other reported damage.
The vehicle is being sold on its Manitoba registration, which serves as the ownership document in Manitoba, Canada.
